<comment type="function">
<text>Catalyzes methyl transfer from S-methylmethionine (SMM) to adenosyl-L-homocysteine (AdoMet). SMM degradation (by HMT-1, HMT-2 and HMT-3) and biosynthesis (by MMT1) constitute the SMM cycle in plants, which is probably required to achieve short term control of AdoMet level.</text>
</comment>
<comment type="catalytic activity">
<reaction evidence="3">
<text>L-homocysteine + S-methyl-L-methionine = H(+) + 2 L-methionine</text>
